@startuml
actor User as U

U --> FlutterApp : Upload Image
U --> FlutterApp : Log in
U --> FlutterApp : View Potholes
U --> FlutterApp : Confirm Detection
U --> FlutterApp : Register
U --> FlutterApp : Logout

box "Client Side (Flutter)"
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : POST /login
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : POST /register
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : POST /logout
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : POST /upload_frame
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : GET /potholes
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : POST /confirm_detection
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : GET /get_detection_confirmation
    FlutterApp --> FlaskServer : GET /get_detected_image
end box

box "Server Side (Flask)"
    FlaskServer --> Database : Authenticate user
    FlaskServer --> Database : Register new user
    FlaskServer --> Database : Log user out
    FlaskServer --> Database : Insert uploaded image
    FlaskServer --> Database : Fetch pothole coordinates
    FlaskServer --> DetectionService : Process detection in image
    DetectionService --> FlaskServer : Notify detection result
    FlaskServer --> Database : Save or update detection result
    FlaskServer --> DetectionService : Confirm detection on request

    FlaskServer --> Database : Update image status (e.g., PROCESSED, CONFIRMED) or delete image
end box

box "Database (PostgreSQL)"
    Database --> FlaskServer : Return user data (login, registration)
    Database --> FlaskServer : Save uploaded image and location data
    Database --> FlaskServer : Fetch pothole coordinates
    Database --> FlaskServer : Update detection status
end box

@enduml
